classDiagram
    %% PawPal+ class design. Keep this file in sync with your Python implementation.

    class Priority {
        <<enumeration>>
        LOW
        MEDIUM
        HIGH
    }

    class Pet {
        +str name
        +str species
        +int age
        +list~str~ special_care_needs
        +add_care_need(need str) None
        +describe() str
    }

    class Owner {
        +str name
        +dict preferences
        +int available_minutes
        +list~Pet~ pets
        +add_pet(pet Pet) None
        +set_availability(minutes int) None
        +get_available_minutes() int
    }

    class Task {
        +str title
        +int duration_minutes
        +Priority priority
        +str description
        +Pet pet
        +priority_score() int
        +describe() str
    }

    class ScheduledItem {
        +str start_time
        +Task task
        +describe() str
    }

    class Scheduler {
        +Owner owner
        +list~Task~ tasks
        +add_task(task Task) None
        +remove_task(task Task) None
        +sort_tasks() list~Task~
        +generate_schedule(start_time str) list~ScheduledItem~
        +explain() str
    }

    Owner "1" *-- "0..*" Pet : owns
    Pet "1" <-- "0..*" Task : has care task
    Scheduler "1" o-- "0..*" Task : manages
    Scheduler "1" --> "1" Owner : plans for
    Scheduler ..> ScheduledItem : produces
    Task --> Priority : uses
    ScheduledItem --> Task : wraps
